==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Starveling
<hw>Starve"ling</hw> <pr>(st⟦aum⟧rv"l⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Starve</ets> + <ets>-ling</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who, or that
which, pines from lack of food, or nutriment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Old Sir John hangs with me, and thou knowest he is no
<qex>starveling</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Starveling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Starveling
<hw>Starve"ling</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Hungry; lean; pining with
want.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Starwort</ent>⟦br⟧
